  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "display_name": "Mark",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. **Look** at your user profile to understand their needs and challenges.\r\n\r\n2. **Drag** each checklist box onto the part of the app where it applies.\r\n\r\n3. **Mark** the box to show how well the design works for your user:\r\n\r\n    * If it works well, color it green or add a check.\r\n    \r\n    * If it doesn't work well, color it red or add an X.\r\n\r\n4. **Point** an arrow to the part of the app that works well or needs improvement.\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**User Profile:**\r\n\r\n\r\n- **Name**: Mark\r\n- **Age**: 68\r\n- Uses a phone daily to read news, text family, and check photos.\r\n- Increases text size and brightness because of vision changes.\r\n- Struggles with small buttons, low contrasting colors, or crowded layouts.\r\n",
    "bubble_choice_description": "Mark uses a mobile phone with large text and high contrast. Help check if the app is easy to read, see, and navigate.",
